  "course_description": "This is the first of a two-semester graduate sequence on partial differential equations (PDEs), with a balance of theory and applications. Topics covered will include solutions and properties of the heat, wave, and Laplace equations; classification of linear PDEs; solution of nonlinear first order PDEs via the method of characteristics, with applications to conservation laws; solution of linear PDEs via the Fourier transform; Sobolev spaces, embeddings, and inequalities; existence theory for elliptic PDEs.",
